I visited this restaurant with a friend who previously ordered food, via online, and wanted to tell the employees personally how much she injoyed the food.  Well, that didn't go too well. The two employees at the first, especially the woman, were not welcoming. The man joked with my friend but the vibe was off.  My friend stated that she wanted to stop by personally and tell the establishment how much she injoyed the food. Which she ordered twice and had delivered. After telling the two employees this, the woman (who was scrolling on her phone at time) said to my friend "oh, I thought you were here to order."  Baffled....  Not a thank you for your compliment, not a come back another time, nothing. I've personally never ate from this restaurant and I doubt I ever will, especially after that awkward moment.  I refuse to allow this experience to set the tone for all Caribbean black businesses.

I wanted to try the new restaurant that I heard the owner of this restaurant opened recently, which was a block or two away from this one and I was excited.  I told all I knew at that were around me at the time.  When I finally got there, the first time I tasted the food I ordered, the taste was off.  I thought I would try again, this time when I tried to order, the woman totally ignored me.  When she finally gave me any attention she gave me the nastiest look, I wondered why is she serving at a restaurant.  And after all of that she continued to ignore me and proceeded to replace some of the silver containers holding the food to be served.  When I realized ordering would be next to impossible at this restaurant, because of the horrible customer service, I went back to the original one where I was served readily and with care.  The  lady at this one served a lot of food and it was quick.  Later on I checked the reciept and I became aware that I was served by the owner herself. Which brings me to come to the opinion that only when the owner is present, the cashiers do their jobs.  Do not discredit the stores because of the bad customer service by the cashiers.  Do what you can to let the management know, because chances are they are not aware of who is causing their business to go down.  I really and truly believe these restaurants would have had lines going around the corner as the food is tasty, but there are customers who would not compromise for good customer service.  The owner seems so nice, if in fact she was the owner, in fact this could be the next Golden Crust if care is taken -who knows...but the cashiers/servers are literally holding back production.
